# gen164 (E1 reflexive): parrot0 reasons about composing its OWN parts. The
# gen160 self-challenge probe walled here; now a composition self-challenge —
# varied surface, held-out — lands in mod_loop with a loop-shaped METHOD over
# real parts (the compose-bench discipline), staying anti-self-management
# (propose, never act). The parts/composition words carry it, so it transfers.
> how would you prove that your subsystems compose, not just work alone?
< I would treat it as a composition self-challenge, not self-management: pick three parts I already have — say knowledge (facts and rules), abduction (the missing premise), and proof — and write ONE held-out dialogue, with fresh names so it cannot be memorized, that needs all three at once; it passes only if they cooperate with no new special-case module. I would ratchet it in English and Italian, bump my version, and journal whether composition held or a seam appeared. I can propose this; an external agent edits, runs the tests, and commits.
